        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 1.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - The Kethiv abandons here the invariable analogy of Chronicles, and reads ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Hiram",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for \"Huram,\" which latter form, however, is replaced in the Keri. Beside this Hiram or Huram, the king, there was another Hiram or Huram, the same king's chief artificer, and whom he sent to the help of Solomon (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 7:13, 40",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
